T*
(CHAPTER I: Introduction) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1.1 Overview) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Predictive maintenance is the use of data and machine-learning models to estimate failure) Tj
T*
(risk before a machine breaks down. Traditional reactive maintenance starts after failure has) Tj
T*
(already caused downtime. Preventive maintenance schedules service at fixed intervals, but) Tj
T*
(this may replace parts too early or too late. Predictive maintenance is more flexible) Tj
T*
(because it uses current machine-condition signals.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(In industrial environments, sensors record temperature, speed, torque, and tool wear. These) Tj
T*
(readings can contain early warning patterns. A machine-learning model can learn from) Tj
T*
(historical examples and classify new machine states as normal or risky.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1.2 Project Goals) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The aim of this project is to build and evaluate a predictive-maintenance model for) Tj
T*
(industrial machines. The project compares multiple algorithms and selects the strongest) Tj
T*
(model using balanced metrics. The main research question is: which machine-learning model) Tj
T*
(can most reliably predict industrial machine failure using sensor features?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(CHAPTER II: Literature Review) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Predictive maintenance is an important application of Industry 4.0 and smart manufacturing.) Tj
T*
(Data-driven maintenance systems use sensor readings to detect patterns that may not be) Tj
T*
(visible through manual inspection. Classification algorithms are useful when the goal is to) Tj
T*
(predict a binary target such as failure or no failure.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Logistic Regression is a common baseline for binary prediction because it estimates failure) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
4 0 obj
<< /Length 2516 >>
stream
BT
/F1 10 Tf
50 790 Td
14 TL
(probability. KNN compares new records with similar historical sensor records. Naive Bayes is) Tj
T*
(a fast probabilistic classifier. Decision Tree models are easy to interpret because they) Tj
T*
(produce rule-based splits. SVM can perform well when a clear separating boundary exists) Tj
T*
(between classes.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Previous predictive-maintenance studies show that accuracy alone can be misleading when) Tj
T*
(failures are rare. A model can achieve high accuracy by predicting the majority class while) Tj
T*
(missing true failures. Therefore, recall, precision, F1-score, and ROC-AUC are important for) Tj
T*
(model selection.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(CHAPTER III: Project Description) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3.1 Dataset Source) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The intended dataset is the Kaggle AI4I 2020 predictive-maintenance dataset. It contains) Tj
T*
(10,000 machine records and 14 columns. The project includes a Kaggle API download script and) Tj
T*
(an offline AI4I-compatible dataset generator for environments where Kaggle access is) Tj
T*
(unavailable.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3.2 Dataset Features) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The main input features are Type, Air temperature [K], Process temperature [K], Rotational) Tj
T*
(speed [rpm], Torque [Nm], and Tool wear [min]. The target variable is Machine failure. The) Tj
T*
(dataset also contains failure-mode columns: TWF, HDF, PWF, OSF, and RNF.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(CHAPTER IV: Data Analysis and Processing) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The preprocessing pipeline validates that all required columns exist. Identifier columns are) Tj
T*
(kept in the dataset but excluded from model features. Machine type is categorical, so it is) Tj
T*
(one-hot encoded. Numeric sensor columns are scaled for Logistic Regression, KNN, Naive) Tj
T*
(Bayes, and SVM because these models are sensitive to feature magnitude. Decision Tree does) Tj
T*
(not require scaling.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The data is split into training and testing sets using stratification so that failure and) Tj
T*
(non-failure classes remain proportionally represented. Class imbalance is handled through) Tj
T*
(class weights in Logistic Regression, Decision Tree, and SVM.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(CHAPTER V: Algorithm and Performance Analysis) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5.1 Logistic Regression) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Logistic Regression estimates the probability that a machine will fail. It is used as a) Tj
T*
(mathematical baseline and supports class weighting for imbalanced data.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5.2 K-Nearest Neighbors) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
