<< /Length 2165 >>
stream
BT
/F1 10 Tf
50 790 Td
14 TL
(KNN classifies a machine based on the labels of nearby records in feature space. It requires) Tj
T*
(scaling because distance calculations are affected by feature magnitudes.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5.3 Naive Bayes) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Naive Bayes applies Bayes' theorem and assumes features are conditionally independent given) Tj
T*
(the class. It is fast and useful as a probabilistic baseline.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5.4 Decision Tree) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Decision Tree learns interpretable rules such as high tool wear, high torque, or abnormal) Tj
T*
(temperature relationships. It is easy to explain but can overfit if not constrained.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5.5 Support Vector Machine) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(SVM finds a separating boundary between failure and non-failure classes. The project uses an) Tj
T*
(RBF kernel and probability estimates for ROC-AUC calculation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5.6 Evaluation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The project evaluates models with accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score, ROC-AUC, confusion) Tj
T*
(matrix, and ROC curve. Recall is especially important because a false negative means a real) Tj
T*
(machine failure was missed.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5.7 Results) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Model results are generated by running python scripts/train_models.py.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(CHAPTER VI: Conclusion) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This project builds a complete predictive-maintenance workflow for industrial machines. It) Tj
T*
(prepares an AI4I-style dataset, trains five machine-learning classifiers, compares them) Tj
T*
(using balanced metrics, and generates report figures and a final academic report. The best) Tj
T*
(model is selected using F1-score, recall, and ROC-AUC rather than accuracy alone. Future) Tj
T*
(improvements may include Random Forest, XGBoost, SHAP feature explanation, real-time IoT) Tj
T*
(integration, and dashboard-based maintenance alerts.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
